def: A tau cross with a loop at the top, used as an attribute orsacred emblem, symbolizing generation or enduring life. Called alsocrux ansata.
Making present. [Obs.] -- Pres`en*tif"ic*ly, adv. [Obs.] Dr. H.More.
Goggles intended to rectify strabismus by permitting visiononly directly in front. Knight.
The act of seizing or taking hold of Catching bargain (Law), abargain made with an heir expectant for the purchase of hisexpectancy at an inadequate price. Bouvier.
The swamp hickory (Carya amara). Its thin-shelled nuts arebitter.
Subsequent. "The graces and gifts of the spirit are postnate."[Archaic] Jer. Taylor.
, v. t. [imp. & p. p. Feoffed; p. pr. & vb. n.. Feoffing.]Etym: [OE. feffen, OF. feffer, fieffer, F. fieffer, fr. fief fief;cf. LL. feoffare, fefare. See Fief.] (Law)
An electric dynamometer having two coils so arranged that onecarries the primary current, and the other the secondary current, ofa transformer.
In an independent manner; without control.
Having, or formed with, a quirk or quirks.
Having two leaflets, as some compound leaves.
